metadata.name: Vlad Dracula Ţepeş
metadata.description:
Vlad Dracula Tepes, better known as Vlad the Impaler, was a Wallachian prince in modern-day Romania in the 15th century. He was a notorious person due to his fondness for impaling his adversaries on long stakes and his cruel ways of retribution.

Despite his reputation for brutality, Vlad was viewed as a staunch defender of his people, frequently standing up to foreign invaders and corrupt officials. He was a superb military strategist who maintained the independence of his small kingdom for a time.


Vlad's rule was cut short when he was betrayed and murdered in combat by his own nobility. However, his memory has endured, inspiring innumerable horror stories and providing the idea for the renowned vampire Count Dracula.
